sql_prompt: Show me all the work order metadata that haven't been modified since they were created
sql: SELECT * FROM DUPLO_WORK_ORDER_METADATA WHERE CREATED_TIME = LAST_MODIFIED_TIME;
sql_context:
create or replace TABLE DUPLO_WORK_ORDER_METADATA (
                    WORK_ORDER_ID VARCHAR(50), --Uniquely identifies a work order
                    WORK_ORDER_METADATA_TYPE VARCHAR(50), --Defines the types of work order metadata (eg. 'includeApproval','includeTrackScript','language', etc.)
                    WORK_ORDER_METADATA_VALUE VARCHAR(300), --Tells the value corresponding to each metadata type (eg. 'true', 'false', NULL, etc.)
                    CREATED_TIME DATE, --Tells the time when this metadata was created
                    CREATED_BY VARCHAR(100), --Tells who is the creator of this work order (eg. 'Airings Event', 'System', etc.)
                    LAST_MODIFIED_TIME DATE, --Tells what time this work order was last updated/modified
                    LAST_MODIFIED_BY VARCHAR(100), --Tells who modified this work order (eg. 'stg_source_insert')
                    ODS_UPDATE_DATE DATE, --Tells us the when it was updated in ods
                    MD5_HASH VARCHAR(100)
                );
